# {{lb|en|psychology|education}} The [[autism spectrum]].
# {{lb|en|chemistry}} The pattern of [[absorption]] or [[emission]] of [[radiation]] produced by a substance when subjected to energy (radiation, heat, electricity, etc.).
# {{lb|en|mathematics|linear algebra}} The set of [[eigenvalue]]s of a [[matrix]].
# {{lb|en|mathematics|functional analysis}} Of a [[bounded]] [[linear operator]] ''A'', the set of [[scalar]] values λ such that the [[operator]] ''A—λI'', where ''I'' denotes the identity operator, does not have a bounded [[inverse]]; intended as a generalisation of the linear algebra sense.
